                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002502"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000110"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Patient mentioned genetic risk for DVT/PE from commercial DNA testing kit of unknown type</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Statement indicating the patient is at risk for a condition or procedure.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>SNOMED:80943009</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>has risk factor</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000057 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000057">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000057</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A reified assertion relating two or more clinical entities, representing a contextualized clinical statement that can carry qualifiers such as negation, uncertainty, and temporality.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Although these structures represent relationships between clinical entities, we model them as reified associations rather than relations, because they represent contextualized assertions with additional attributes (e.g., negation, uncertainty, temporality), which cannot be expressed using binary object properties in OWL.
These relations include the most frequently documented relation types as defined in:
Colicchio, Tiago K., Pavithra I. Dissanayake, and James J. Cimino. &quot;Formal representation of patients’ care context data: the path to improving the electronic health record.&quot; Journal of the American Medical Informatics Association 27, no. 11 (2020): 1648-1657.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>CLCO represents temporal information through four orthogonal mechanisms: (1) temporal_frame (qualifier axis) -- document-relative context via has_temporal_frame, values historical/current/future/hypothetical; (2) completion_status (qualifier axis) -- workflow state via has_completion_status, values pending/in_progress/completed; (3) datatype time properties (data axis) -- computable timestamps via has_start_time, has_end_time, has_duration_value with xsd typed literals; (4) reified temporal associations (entity axis) -- narrative temporal entities such as has_onset, has_date, has_duration where the temporal expression is a first-class clinical_entity linked via has_object. These mechanisms are independent: a single association may carry values from any combination.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>clinical association</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000058 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000058">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000058</oboInOwl:id>
        <owl:equivalentClass>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000057"/>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002501"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000107"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </owl:equivalentClass>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000003"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>He was given Zofran and meclizine at Urgent Care.</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Inference about the location or setting where a clinical event happened.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>OMOP_CONCEPT_ID:32462</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>has setting</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000060 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000060">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000060</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000068"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Modifies a relation to indicate that the relation is intended rather than actual. Boolean.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Epistemic modality axis: captures whether the association describes an actual event or an intended/planned one. Orthogonal to temporal_frame (CLCO_0000082), which captures WHEN relative to the document, and completion_status (CLCO_0000063), which captures workflow state. An intended event may be past (we intended chemo but did not start), present, or future.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>intention</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000062 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000062">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000062</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000068"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The modified relationship is recommended, for example an intervention, admission or some action. Boolean.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>recommended</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000063 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000063">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000063</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000068"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The workflow completion state of a process. Orthogonal to temporal_frame (which captures when relative to the document) and intention (which captures intent). A process may be pending regardless of whether its temporal frame is past, present, or future.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Refactored from the original &quot;status&quot; class. Children include pending (moved from temporal), in_progress, and completed. Aligns with SNOMED procedure status qualifier values and EHR order status fields. No equivalent in NLP temporal annotation schemes like THYME or I2b2.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>OMOP_CONCEPT_ID:4138595</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>SNOMED:40642538</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>completion status</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000065 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000065">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000065</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000063"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>CT results pending</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The process described by the association has been initiated (e.g., ordered, requested) but has not yet reached its terminal output state. This is a workflow status, not a temporal frame: a pending result may refer to a process that occurred in the past (e.g., labs drawn yesterday, results pending).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Moved from subClassOf temporal (CLCO_0000064) to subClassOf completion_status (CLCO_0000063). The previous definition conflated workflow state with temporal frame and epistemic modality. See temporal_plan.txt Section 1A for rationale.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>SNOMED:385645004</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>pending</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000067</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A modifier that provides additional context to a clinical association, such as temporal frame, certainty, negation, or participant-level detail.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>association qualifier</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000068 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000068">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000068</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An association qualifier that modifies the entire clinical statement, such as intention, recommendation or completion status.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Qualifiers for the entire statement.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>statement qualifier</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000069 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000069">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000069</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An association qualifier that modifies only the predicate (relationship type) of a clinical association, rather than the entire statement.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>For situations where the modifier of the predicate is different from the overall statement, these are likely to be rare.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>predicate qualifier</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000071 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000071">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000071</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000025"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002501"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000106"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002502"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Bone density is decreasing; cancer progression is rapid.</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A finding association specifying which facet, part, or functional dimension of an entity is being referred to in the assertion.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Aspect refers to which facet, part, or functional dimension of an entity is being referred to in the assertion. For example density or progression in bone density or cancer progression.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>has aspect</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000072 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000072">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000072</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000025"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002501"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000112"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002502"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>The lesion is located on the anterior aspect of the left knee.</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A finding association specifying the spatial orientation or anatomical direction of a finding relative to a body site.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Spatial orientation qualifiers reuse PATO quality terms directly; CLCO defines only the attachment role.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>has spatial orientation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000073 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000073">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000073</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000025"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002501"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000112"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002502"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Right-sided pneumothorax; bilateral knee pain.</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A finding association specifying the laterality (left, right, bilateral, unilateral, or midline) of a finding relative to a body site.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>laterality_qualifier
  ⊑ has_participant_qualifier only
     (PATO:0000611  # left
      or PATO:0000612  # right
      or PATO:0000613  # bilateral
      or PATO:0000614  # unilateral
      or PATO:0000610) # midline</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>has laterality</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


