                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0002502"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom>
                    <owl:Class>
                        <owl:unionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101"/>
                            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000102"/>
                            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000111"/>
                        </owl:unionOf>
                    </owl:Class>
                </owl:someValuesFrom>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>The pink sputum suggests hemoptysis.</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A finding or condition suggested by a diagnostic process, documentation, another finding or condition, or an intervention.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>suggests finding</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000080 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000080">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000080</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>&quot;Patient denies chest pain&quot; (statement-level); &quot;Tenderness is present, but not in the right upper quadrant&quot; (participant-level).</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Signifies that the qualified element is negated. Applies at any scope: statement-level negation negates the entire association; participant-level negation negates a specific subject or object.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>negation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000081 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000081">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000081</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Signifies that the qualified element is uncertain or suspected. Applies at any scope: statement-level uncertainty qualifies the entire association; participant-level uncertainty qualifies a specific subject or object.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>uncertainty</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000082 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000082">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000082</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000067"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The temporal location of the association relative to the moment of clinical documentation. Orthogonal to completion_status and intention.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Replaces the deprecated temporal (CLCO_0000064). Aligns with THYME DocTimeRel and MedSpaCy temporal context flags. This axis answers WHEN relative to the document, not whether a process is complete (completion_status) or committed (intention).</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>biolink:temporal_context_qualifier</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>temporal frame</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000083 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000083">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000083</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000082"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Patient underwent two kidney transplants (2002, 2012)</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The association describes an event or state that occurred before the time of the clinical document.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>THYME:DocTimeRel_BEFORE</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>historical</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000084 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000084">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000084</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000082"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Currently on metformin</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The association describes an event or state that overlaps with the time of the clinical document.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>THYME:DocTimeRel_OVERLAP</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>current</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000085 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000085">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000085</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000082"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Chemotherapy will begin next Tuesday</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The association describes an event or state that is expected to occur after the time of the clinical document.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>THYME:DocTimeRel_AFTER</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>future</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000086 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000086">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000086</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000082"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>If fever persists, start vancomycin</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The association describes a conditional or contingent event that may or may not occur depending on specified circumstances.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Sits at the boundary of temporal frame and modality. Placed under temporal_frame because NLP systems (THYME contextual_modality, MedSpaCy is_hypothetical) treat it as a document-context label at the same annotation layer as historical/current/future.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>THYME:contextual_modality_HYPOTHETICAL</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>hypothetical</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000087 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000087">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000087</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000063"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Antibiotics course ongoing</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The process described by the association is actively executing but has not yet reached its terminal state.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>in progress</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000088 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000088">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000088</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000063"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112>Physical therapy completed</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The process described by the association has reached its terminal output state.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>completed</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000100 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000100">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000100</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000001"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A core clinical entity over which all clinical context associations occur.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>The 14 core clinical entity classes defined in:
Colicchio, Tiago K., Pavithra I. Dissanayake, and James J. Cimino. &quot;Formal representation of patients’ care context data: the path to improving the electronic health record.&quot; Journal of the American Medical Informatics Association 27, no. 11 (2020): 1648-1657.
All of these should correspond to a subject or object in relations extracted by NLP systems. The exception to that is patient which may be inferred.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:label>clinical entity</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000101">
        <oboInOwl:id>CLCO:0000101</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000100"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A clinical finding of any type, including conditions.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Was finding/condition in original paper, can treat condition as a subclass if needed.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>biolink:DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <rdfs:label>finding</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000102 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CLCO_0000102">
